"use strict";(self.webpackChunktechtalkjohn=self.webpackChunktechtalkjohn||[]).push([[477],{10:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"HypeCycle.mdx","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/HypeCycle.mdx","editUrl":"https://github.com/facebook/docusaurus/edit/main/website/blog/blog/HypeCycle.mdx","source":"@site/blog/HypeCycle.mdx","title":"Hype Cycle","description":"Version 0.1.0","date":"2021-11-12T23:28:32.521Z","formattedDate":"November 12, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":1.29,"truncated":false,"authors":[],"nextItem":{"title":"TechTalkJohn","permalink":"/blog/techTalkBack.mdx"}},"content":"Version 0.1.0\\n---\\n\\n\\nI am an Electronics and Software Engineer specializing in  hardware and software technology disciplines\\n\\nI have decades of hands-on experience with some of the ever changing Electronic, Internet, and Software technologies. I have a passion pursuing what\u2019s new and improved with these industries. \\n\\nChecking out what\u2019s new or not, a pipe dream or not, or what\u2019s new and improved, is like panning for gold. Buried within the mountains of info rubble produced daily, every so often one finds interesting technology nuggets making the effort worthwhile.\\n\\nThe Electronic, Internet, and Software industries are probably the fastest changing endeavors mankind has ever created. The half life of many  products making it to market are relatively short. There are some very short lived  and some that were just vapor. \\n\\nThe Hype Cycle helps separate reality from fiction.\\n\\n![Hype Cycle](/img/images/HypeCycle.png )\\n\\nThe  Hype Cycle points of interest   are:\\n\\n- Technology Trigger  \\nA potential technology breakthrough happens.\\n\\n- Peak of Inflated Expectations   \\nEarly publicity produces a number of success stories and often accompanied by stories of failures. Some companies may take defect corrective action but most don\u2019t.\\n\\n- Trough of Disillusionment  \\nInterest wanes as experiments and implementations fail to deliver on the hype.\\n\\n- Slope of Enlightenment  \\nTechnology consumers begin to understand the technology better and how it may benefit them.\\n\\n- Plateau of Productivity  \\nMainstream adoption starts to take off.\\n\\nThe few technologies that make it to the Plateau of Productivity, some may be doomed  to the spiral of death by inattention to details for keeping products alive\\n\\n---"},{"id":"techTalkBack.mdx","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/techTalkBack.mdx","editUrl":"https://github.com/facebook/docusaurus/edit/main/website/blog/blog/techTalkBack.mdx","source":"@site/blog/techTalkBack.mdx","title":"TechTalkJohn","description":"Docusaurus","date":"2021-11-12T21:46:39.769Z","formattedDate":"November 12, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.065,"truncated":false,"authors":[],"prevItem":{"title":"Hype Cycle","permalink":"/blog/HypeCycle.mdx"}},"content":"##  Docusaurus \\n\\nTechTalkJohn is built  using using [Docusaurus](https://docusaurus.io) , and hosted on [Vercel](https://vercel.com/home)."}]}')}}]);